"Gruza G.V., Ran'kova E.Ya.","Climate oscillations and changes over Russia",2003,"Izvestiya - Atmospheric and Ocean Physics","39","2",,"145","162",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0037647551&partnerID=40&md5=0debcb866bf1e9d2923039a137bedf59","Institute of Global Climate/Ecology, Glebovskaya ul. 20b, Moscow 107532, Russian Federation","Gruza, G.V., Institute of Global Climate/Ecology, Glebovskaya ul. 20b, Moscow 107532, Russian Federation; Ran'kova, E.Ya., Institute of Global Climate/Ecology, Glebovskaya ul. 20b, Moscow 107532, Russian Federation","Refined definitions of a climate, climatic variables, climate variability, climate changes, and climate monitoring that are applicable to the analysis of climate variability from observations in the case of a changing climate are given. The main features of global warming are described. New data are reported on the features of climate changes over Russia in the second half of the 20th century and on changes in climate anomaly and extremeness. Empirical estimates for the local sensitivity of air temperature to changes in the greenhouse gas concentration are discussed. The estimates can be used to assess the expected temperature changes in the coming 20-25 years.",,"climate change; global warming; temperature anomaly; twentieth century; Russian Federation",,,,,,"(1992) Vsemirnaya Klimaticheskaya Programma 1992-2001 Gg. Tretii Dolgosrochnyi Plan VMO, Chast'II, Tom II (1992-2001 World Climate Program. Third WMO Long-Range Plan), 2 (762 PART 2). , VMO; (2001) Climate Change 2001. The Scientific Basis. Contribution of Working Group 1 to the Third Assessment Report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC), , Houghton, J.T., Ding, Y., Griggs, D.J., Noguer, M., Van der Linden, P.J., and Xiaosu, D., Eds., Cambridge: Cambridge Univ. Press; Jones, P.D., New, M., Parker, D.E., Martin, S., Rigor, I.G., Surface air temperature and its changes over the past 150 years (1999) Rev. Geophys., 37, pp. 173-199; Izrael, Yu.A., Global system of observations. Prediction and assessment of changes in the state of environment. Principles of monitoring (1974) Meteorol. Gidrol., 7, pp. 3-8; Gruza, G.V., Ran'kova, E.Ya., Monitoring and probabilistic forecast of short-period climate oscillations (1989) Shest'desyat Let Tsentru Gidrometeorologicheskikh Prognozov (60th Anniversary of the Center for Hydrometeorological Forecasts), pp. 148-170. , Leningrad: Gidrometeoizdat; (1999) Obzor Zagryazneniya Prirodnoi Sredy V Rossiiskoi Federatsii Za 1999 G. (Review of Environmental Pollution in Russia for 1999), , St. Petersburg: Gidrometeoizdat; Jones, P.D., Hemispheric surface air temperature variations: A reanalysis and an update to 1993 (1994) J. Clim., 7, pp. 1794-1802; Folland, C.K., Parker, D.E., Correction of instrumental biases in historical sea surface temperature data (1995) Q. J. R. Meteorol. Soc., 121, pp. 319-367; Ran'kova, E.Ya., Gruza, G.V., Indicators of climate change for Russia (1998) Meteorol. Gidrol., 1; Gruza, G., Rankova, E., Razuvaev, V., Bulygina, O., Indicators of climate change for the Russian federation (1999) Clim. Change, 42, pp. 212-242; Gruza, G.V., Ran'kova, E.Ya., Estimation of the climate response to changes in greenhouse gas concentration from surface air temperature observations over Russia (1999) Izv. Akad. Nauk, Fiz. Atmos. Okeana, 35 (6), pp. 742-749. , Izv., Atmos. Ocean. Phys. (Engl. Transl.), vol. 35, no. 6, pp. 671-678; Tett, S.F.B., Johns, T.C., Mitchell, J.F.B., Global and regional variability in a coupled AOGCM (1997) Clim. Dyn., 13, pp. 303-323","Gruza, G.V.; Institute of Global Climate/Ecology, Glebovskaya ul. 20b, Moscow 107532, Russian Federation; email: gruza@newmail.ru",,,,,,,,00014338,,,,"English","Izv. Atmos. Ocean Phys.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0037647551
